issue.body:
- Deployer version: 7.0.2
- Deployment OS: Alpine

The first deployment always fails because of this error.

```php
task('deploy:update_code', function (): void {
    if (has('previous_release')) {
        run('cp -aT {{previous_release}}/ {{release_path}}/ || true');
    }

    // ...rest of task
})

task('deploy', [
    'deploy:setup',
    'deploy:lock',
    'deploy:release',
    'deploy:update_code',
    'deploy:shared',
    'deploy:writable',
    'deploy:clear_paths',
    'deploy:symlink',
    'deploy:unlock',
    'deploy:cleanup',
    'deploy:success',
]);
```

`deploy:release` is running before `deploy:update_code` which makes the call to `has('previous_release')` so I'm not sure why this happens. Is there something missing here? Running the deploy again after works.

